cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as word segmentation, part-of-speech tagging, and named entity recognition. Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks and deep learning techniques further supports this categorization. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the use of deep learning models for the lexical analysis task. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the development of an end-to-end model for natural language understanding. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for the lexical analysis task. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the processing of text data, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks.
